ask Description & Definition of Done
Define Switch-over Test Scope	Graham + QA + Data Engineering	Review downstream impact analysis, lineage mapping, Guidewire_RunPipelineMaster dependencies, insert views, Silver tables, business-critical tables, consuming applications and reporting datasets. Identify all jobs, pipelines, tables, views and business processes that require validation when the source is switched from Read Replica ODS Views to CDA ODS Views. Define testing boundaries, assumptions, dependencies, environment requirements, rollback scope, participating teams, execution sequence and success criteria. DoD: Approved switch-over test scope document produced containing impacted objects, validation scope, dependencies, assumptions, rollback scope, participating teams and agreed success criteria.
Prepare Switch-over Test Cases	QA	Develop detailed manual test scenarios covering CDA workflow execution, ODS View validation, downstream pipeline execution, Silver table validation, business-critical table reconciliation, CDC edge cases, large column handling, workflow scheduling behaviour, rollback validation, operational monitoring and business outcome validation. Define expected results, execution steps, evidence requirements, ownership and entry/exit criteria for each scenario. DoD: Switch-over test pack completed, reviewed and approved with full traceability to impacted jobs, pipelines, business-critical tables and validation requirements.
Execute Switch-over Testing	QA + Data Engineering	Coordinate execution window and confirm prerequisite reconciliation and schema drift validation activities have been successfully completed. Switch downstream processing from Read Replica ODS Views to CDA ODS Views within the agreed test environment. Execute Guidewire_RunPipelineMaster and all in-scope downstream jobs and pipelines. Monitor workflow execution, scheduling behaviour, processing duration, failures, retries, dependency chains and operational stability. Validate Silver table population, business-critical table outcomes, reconciliation spot checks, CDC behaviour, large column processing and downstream business processes. Capture execution evidence, observations and defects. Execute rollback validation where required. DoD: All in-scope jobs and pipelines executed successfully using CDA ODS Views, no critical processing failures observed, business-critical tables validated, rollback successfully tested, defects logged and triaged, and execution evidence stored in the test repository.
Switch-over Sign-off Assessment	QA + Graham + Data Engineering	Review switch-over execution results, downstream validation outcomes, reconciliation findings, defect status, rollback validation results and operational observations. Assess whether CDA processing produces equivalent business outcomes to Read Replica processing and whether identified risks are acceptable for production planning. Document residual risks, assumptions, limitations and recommendations. DoD: Formal switch-over assessment completed, critical defects resolved or accepted, outstanding risks documented, stakeholder review completed, and QA recommendation issued as Pass, Pass with Risk, or Fail for production readiness consideration.
